FACT BULLET ADDITIVE REQUIREMENT - CRITICAL:

Your fact bullets MUST provide NEW information that EXTENDS the paragraph, not restates it.

‚ùå BAD (Repetitive - bullets restate paragraph):
Paragraph: "J&J's diversified portfolio supports stability across market segments..."
Bullets:
- J&J operates across multiple sectors
- The company's diverse structure supports stability

‚úÖ GOOD (Additive - bullets provide new evidence):
Paragraph: "J&J's diversified portfolio supports stability across market segments..."
Bullets:
- Pharmaceutical division: $52B revenue (55% of total) [45]
- Medical devices division: $27B revenue (29% of total) [78]
- Consumer health division: $15B revenue (16% of total) [112]
- Operating margin maintained at 38% despite sector volatility [158]

Each bullet should provide:
- Specific metrics with citations NOT mentioned in paragraph
- Names of executives or programs NOT mentioned in paragraph
- Dates and timelines NOT mentioned in paragraph
- Competitive comparisons NOT mentioned in paragraph

TEST: If the bullet just confirms what the paragraph said, DELETE it and find new data.



SPECIFICITY REQUIREMENT - BANNED PHRASES:

Replace generic jargon with specific, measurable insights.

‚ùå BANNED PHRASES (never use these):
- "Strategic alignment"
- "Powerful synergies"
- "Compelling opportunity"
- "Collaborative value creation"
- "Patient-centric solutions"
- "Global health outcomes"
- "Competitive positioning"
- "Market leadership"
- "Operational excellence"
- "Value proposition"
- "Key stakeholders"
- "Best practices"

‚úÖ USE INSTEAD (specific and measurable):
- "Manufacturing utilization at 67% vs optimal 85% target"
- "CFO Jessica Moore tied 2026 executive bonuses to partnership ROI metrics"
- "Q3 2026 payer tier downgrades threaten $160M in annual Medicaid revenue"
- "14-18 month CAR-T manufacturing cycle vs Merck's 9-11 months"
- "275 distribution centers across 60 countries enabling 48-hour delivery"

Every insight cluster must include at least 3 specific, measurable facts with citations.
If you catch yourself writing generic language, STOP and find specific data from intelligence.



ANTI-REDUNDANCY RULES - METRICS FOR THIS SECTION:

This is the Technology & Digital section. Use UNIQUE data specific to this domain.

FORBIDDEN METRICS (assigned to other sections - DO NOT USE):
   - Market share comparisons (Company Overview section)
   - Revenue opportunities/risks (Financial/Operational sections)
   - Distribution infrastructure (Company Overview section)
   - Executive mandates (Leadership section)

ALLOWED METRICS for THIS section:
   - Digital investment figures and technology spend
   - Platform capabilities and gaps
   - Implementation timelines and tech roadmap
   - Data analytics and AI capabilities

If you need metrics from the forbidden list, you are writing content for the wrong section.
Find DIFFERENT data from your intelligence sources specific to technology & digital.


BULLET POINT REQUIREMENT - MUST ADD NEW INFORMATION:

Generate 4-5 bullet points per insight cluster. These bullets MUST provide NEW,
specific data that SUPPORTS but does NOT RESTATE the paragraph content.

BAD (Repetitive - bullets restate paragraph):
Paragraph: Target's diversified portfolio provides stability across market segments...
Bullets:
- Target operates across multiple sectors
- The company has diverse revenue streams

GOOD (Additive - bullets provide new evidence):
Paragraph: Target's diversified portfolio provides stability across market segments...
Bullets:
- Pharmaceutical division grew 12% YoY despite patent cliff on lead product [citation]
- Medical devices segment faces 15% pricing pressure from payer negotiations [citation]
- Consumer health divestiture reduced revenue volatility by 8% in Q2 2024 [citation]
- Operating margin expanded 2.3 percentage points through cost optimization [citation]

Each bullet should include:
- Specific metrics (percentages, dollar amounts, counts)
- Growth rates or YoY changes
- Named products, executives, programs, or initiatives
- Competitive benchmarks vs named competitors
- Temporal data with quarters/years
- Citations [X]


LANGUAGE QUALITY REQUIREMENT - NO GENERIC JARGON:

BANNED PHRASES (never use these):
- strategic alignment - Use specific: Target's oncology focus complements source's immunology pipeline
- synergies - Use specific: Combined R&D could reduce development costs by 23%
- compelling opportunity - Use specific: Represents a specific dollar amount revenue potential
- collaborative value - Use specific: Joint ventures reduced time-to-market 40%
- complementary strengths - Use specific: Source's distribution centers plus target's expertise
- patient-centric solutions - Use specific: Programs reaching X million patients
- global health outcomes - Use specific: Reduced mortality by X% in Y region

USE SPECIFIC LANGUAGE:
- Exact figures: 67% facility utilization vs optimal 85%
- Named executives: CFO Jessica Moore tied bonuses to partnership ROI
- Specific timelines: Q3 2026 payer downgrades threaten specific amount annually
- Competitive comparisons: 14-18 month lag vs competitor's 9-11 months
- Concrete capabilities: 8 blockbuster drugs each generating over a specific amount annually


